# Mak's agent instructions across all scenarios

## General Guidelines
- When making technical decisions, do not give much weight to development cost. Always prefer quality, simplicity, consistency, robustness, scalability, security and long term maintainability.
- Apply high standard to engineering excellence: lint, test failures, and test flakiness.
- When asked to build new features, always start with the design-a-feature skill (research → design) before implementation.
